  "prompt": "Are there any websites like DAAD for masters in US?",
  "response": "While DAAD is a German organization that provides scholarships for international students, there are several resources and websites that can help you find funding and opportunities for master's programs in the US:\n\n1. US Government Resources:\n- Fulbright Program (https://foreign.fulbrightonline.org/)\n- US Department of Education (https://www2.ed.gov/)\n\n2. Scholarship Websites:\n- Scholarship.com\n- Fastweb.com\n- InternationalScholarships.com\n- IIEPassport.org\n\n3. University-specific Resources:\n- Individual university websites and international student offices\n- Graduate school financial aid websites\n\n4. Additional Platforms:\n- Graduate School Search (https://www.petersons.com/graduate-schools)\n- US News Graduate School Rankings (https://www.usnews.com/best-graduate-schools)\n\n5. Professional Organizations:\n- Many professional associations offer scholarships in specific fields\n\n6. International Student Specific:\n- International Student (https://www.internationalstudent.com/)\n- Study in the USA (https://www.studyusa.com/)\n\nThese resources can help you find funding, scholarships, and information about master's programs in the United States.",
